        I18N::translate(
            'For every fully-dated child in the tree (BIRT carrying both a day and a month) the widget groups siblings in the same FAM whose BIRT julian-days fall within one day of each other into a multiple-birth set. Matching on date proximity rather than the exact day means cross-midnight twins (e.g. 31 December / 1 January) still merge: a single mother cannot place two separate pregnancies a calendar day apart, so the shared family plus the close birth dates are the signal by themselves. The chart draws one series per multiplicity that actually occurs in the tree (twins, triplets, quadruplets, quintuplets and above) — each series shows that multiplicity\'s per-century share of all dated births. Year-only BIRT records (day and month both blank) are intentionally excluded — they would turn every "0 0 1829" sibling group into a phantom multi-birth set. Centuries below 200 fully-dated children are dropped to keep the curve from spiking on small denominators.'
        ),
        $aboutThisChart,
